Just a shout to all Who fans. And Lady Morag? By the end of the Doctor's 7th incarnation (McCoy) he had changed the interior quite a bit. You see most of this in the Doctor Who movie that gives us number 8, played by Paul McGann. Sometime after that and before the first Eccelson episode, he went through many adventures, an entire Time War, and another regeneration. Methinks a lot can happen in the midst of all that. Not the least of which being he obviously had to make MANY repairs and rebuilds using substandard parts and facilities. Go figure.

Actually, in one episode, the different look of the tardis is explained. It's a visual theme that can be selected at the doctors choosing. I think he even uses a word like 'desktop theme' or 'system theme'. If I'm not mistaken it's either one of the episodes where Sarah Jane makes an appearance or the episode 'Time Crash' I'm not sure, I think it might even be one of the season four finale episodes (which feature Sarah Jane). It is interesting though, people always assume that everything in science fiction has to have a logical reason, but asthetics and ceremony would play a part too, especially with time lords as they are known as being sanctimonious and pompous.
And excuse my horrible manners, thanks for the upload!
